    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving powerplant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,400 RPM redline. Mated to a desirable 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission and an M Variable Differential Lock, the chassis dynamics remain sharp and predictable. The vehicle is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) for adjustable damping rates across varying surfaces. Recent preventative maintenance includes rod bearing replacement and updated throttle actuators, ensuring the mechanical integrity of the valvetrain and bottom end. The subframe bushings remain stiff, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback enthusiasts crave. A driver-focused specimen ready for the B-roads.",
